From the latter point of view, all current technologies are not good enough for us - this adds work to algorithm designers.
That is, it is necessary to remember not only about the resolution on the X and Y axes, but also Z.
Speed, the number of frames per second is also very important.
Human movements are quite dynamic, and the current 30 k/s is frankly not enough, especially for gestures.
Stephen Betiches of our Redmond lab made a touch sensor with adjustable latency processing - from 1 to 100 ms, with modern serial sensors closer to the second (60-100) indicator.
