- In my lectures, I often say that augmented reality is the seventh breakthrough in the interaction of man and machine.
I think the eighth may well be an additive tactile sensations.
In the meantime, one of the interesting tricks is the use of the second hand as a kind of substrate for the image.
She's a good press recorder!
