And if Sweden, as its legislation perfectly permits, and as it has done in other cases, interrogates Sen. Assange at the Ecuadorian Embassy in London or interrogates him via Skype, tomorrow this problem will be exhausted.
Correa took the opportunity to prove himself as a defender of freedom of the press and stressed that he does not tolerate “mediocre, dishonesty and lies that distort freedom of expression.”
